      "weather": "FINE",
      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCHINVAR COSMO (2) looks close to win after hitting the frame last run (26.22) at Geelong in a Grade 5. Has first look at box 2 this time. Goes very well at the trip finding the frame in each of four starts. One of the leading chances. SHE REBEL (4) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish one length away in third (22.53) behind Paw Clarissa at this track. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Bold showing expected. DOONGALLA DON (6) wasn't far away at the finish when 5th and beaten only 5 lengths (30.04) at Sandown. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. PAW WELKES (8) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish as public elect.",
